    "body" : "JFR was originally a proprietary feature of the Oracle JDK, so -XX:+UnlockCommercialFeatures applies only to Oracle JDK.  Oracle JDK 11 emits a warning when using the -XX:+UnlockCommercialFeatures option, whereas OpenJDK doesn’t recognize this option and reports an error. (ref <a href=\"https://dzone.com/articles/using-java-flight-recorder-with-openjdk-11-1\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">dzone.com/articles/using-java-flight-recorder-with-openjdk-1&zwnj;&#8203;1-1</a>)"
  } ],
